    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Ann Arbor Staging System - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ann_arbor_staging_system">Ann Arbor Staging System</xref>
 is a system for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cancer_staging">CANCER STAGING</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ann_arbor_staging_system">Ann Arbor Staging System</xref>
 is the staging system for lymphomas, both in Hodgkin Lymphoma and Non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL).        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ann_arbor_staging_system">Ann Arbor Staging System</xref>
 has generally the same function as the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_tnm_staging_system">TNM Staging System</xref>
 in solid 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumours</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cancer_staging">CANCER STAGINGS</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=21104336"
               scope="external"
               format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
